Responses.NAM1 - Response Text: The name sounds familiar... Perhaps you should speak with the Saren family.
They have a manor in the Redoran Plaza.
I heard she was disgraced and living somewhere here in Vivec.
Perhaps you should speak with the Saren family who live in the Redoran Plaza.
I think she has a shop somewhere around here in St. Olms.
I believe Nalvilie Saren is a shopkeeper in Vivec.
Surprisingly, I haven't thought about her at all recently.
I will try and forget about her.
She refused to even see me?
I feared she would be too proud to accept charity, but I didn't expect her to reject me again so soundly.
Well, you did find her, and so I shall give you my support on the council.
Nalvilie Saren was an acquaintance of mine... I was quite fond of her and have often wondered what happened to her.
I believe the Saren family lives in the Redoran Compound in Vivec. That may be a good place to start.
When you find her, tell that I do not care what happened in the past and that I can support her. Invite her to meet with me here in Ald'ruhn.
She has disgraced herself and her family.
I do not understand why my Lord would still wish to find her after the way she treated him.
Sometimes I wish... But no, it would not be proper.
She had disgraced our family. I will not say more.
She is no longer my daughter.
It is impolite to speak of such things.
If I tell you, will you leave here and promise to never mention the subject in my presence again?
Nalvilie Saren is disgraced. Please do not remind me of this.
I do not wish to discuss it.
She lives near here in St. Olms Canalworks South-One. I'm glad my brother warned me about her before she could test her favors on me.
Yes, I knew her. I sometimes wish I didn't. It's not a good thing these days to have been one of her lovers.
If you really want to see her, she lives near here, in St. Olms Canalworks South-One.
I see her now and then, though we're not close like we used to be, before I realized what her game was.
I think she has a shop on the south side of the Canalworks.
Nalvilie? Yes, I remember her. I don't know where she is now, though.
Yes, she is 'much blown upon' as the Ashlanders would say. A disgrace... Though I must admit I enjoyed her favors myself many years ago.
She lives in the St. Olms Canton now. I believe she runs a shop there.
Nalvilie? Yes, I knew her. I knew her quite well, in fact. I haven't seen her in years.
Nalvilie... Now that's a name I haven't heard in years. I heard she's had some hard times after she lost her youth and beauty.
Yes, I remember her. We grew up together in Vivec. She always had a man on each arm.
I haven't heard that name in years... I have many fond memories of her, but I don't know where she is now.
Speak with the Saren family. Their manor is nearby.
